President Trump held a Cabinet meeting to discuss the progress made during his recent trip to Europe and to focus on workforce training. He highlighted the success of the economy, with over 3.6 million jobs created since the election and historically low unemployment rates for various demographic groups. The administration is now focusing on workforce training to meet the demand for skilled workers as more companies move back to the United States. Ivanka Trump, Secretary of Labor Alexander Acosta, Secretary of Commerce Wilbur Ross, Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos, and Administrator of the Small Business Administration Linda McMahon spoke about the actions being taken to expand vocational education and on-the-job training. The President also mentioned upcoming announcements regarding workforce training initiatives and trade negotiations with Mexico and the European Union. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo discussed recent developments with North Korea, NATO, and Mexico. Other Cabinet members, including Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue and Secretary of Housing and Urban Development Ben Carson, also provided updates on their respective areas. The President concluded the meeting by stating his commitment to addressing drug pricing and thanking the Cabinet members for their work.